



1) Install psql

from linux prompt
	$ sudo apt-get update
	$ sudo apt-get install postgresql postgresql-contrib

2) Login as defaul user
from linux promt
	$ sudo su - postgres 
	$ psql

3) create a new database
Do step 2, at the prompt
  	# create database testdbname;

4) create a user
  	# create user username with password 'myPassword';
  	# grant all privileges on database dvdrental to username;

exit and return to linux prompt
5) Log back the database using the new user name 

	$ psql -d testdbname -U username

  


  

  
